This paper deals with wireless cellular networks and their coverage, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of base stations and their placement can also be considered as a problem in optimization and modeling (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the use of simulations and approximations, which are common in data science (cs.DS) and computational intelligence (cs.SI).
